@zoff99 I still have the feeling this is needed for better stickers handling. Your proposal is looking fine but isn't it out-of-scope about stickers/inline stuffs as your proposal is about text messages? (Correct me if I am wrong ofc)

This file kind just would allows to handle stickers/images/videos/musics inline. I'm sure I could even add some methods ie. `friend_send_sticker()`, `friend_send_inline_image()`, `group_sticker_send()`, etc.

Of course this would need to be adjusted to the MessageV2 proposal format so it remains compatible and your "standard" gains stickers/inline images/videos/music with the features you just listed.

@iphydf i am opposed to enums without specific number values.
can we start making this more "sane" please in the future.

like this:

```
enum TOX_FILE_KIND {
TOX_FILE_KIND_DATA 0,
TOX_FILE_KIND_AVATAR 1,
};
```

this way when we deprecate an item in the future, the values will stay the same
